{{Quote|They're certain to be at the swap, and we'll finally put you where you belong. You must follow our ways, Khea. A female just cannot abandon her role in the tribe and the meets. It's dangerous.|[[Jek Nkik]], to [[Aguilae|Khea Nkul]]|<ref name="SP">{{JournalCite|11|Spare Parts (short story)|reprint=1}}</ref>}}
A '''swap meet''' was a means of bartering between [[Jawa/Legends|Jawas]]. One, the [[Great Swap Meet]], also known as Dune Sea Haggleday, was held in the [[Dune Sea/Legends|Dune Sea]]. At these meets, Jawas would arrange marriages for clan members and trade between each other. Swap meets were considered large social gatherings between many clans of the Jawas.

